6549 return CI && CI->getValue().ult(C->getType()->getIntegerBitWidth());
6550 });
6551
6552 return Safe;
6553}
6554
6555enum class UndefPoisonKind {
6556 PoisonOnly = (1 << 0),
6557 UndefOnly = (1 << 1),
6558 UndefOrPoison = PoisonOnly | UndefOnly,
6559};
6560
6561static bool includesPoison(UndefPoisonKind Kind) {
6562 return (unsigned(Kind) & unsigned(UndefPoisonKind::PoisonOnly)) != 0;
6563}
6564
6565static bool includesUndef(UndefPoisonKind Kind) {
6566 return (unsigned(Kind) & unsigned(UndefPoisonKind::UndefOnly)) != 0;
6567}
6568
6569static bool canCreateUndefOrPoison(const Operator *Op, UndefPoisonKind Kind,
6570 bool ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata) {
6571
6572 if (ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata && includesPoison(Kind) &&
6573 Op->hasPoisonGeneratingFlagsOrMetadata())
6574 return true;
6575
6576 unsigned Opcode = Op->getOpcode();
6577
6578 // Check whether opcode is a poison/undef-generating operation
6579 switch (Opcode) {
6580 case Instruction::Shl:
6581 case Instruction::AShr:
6582 case Instruction::LShr:
6583 return includesPoison(Kind) && !shiftAmountKnownInRange(Op->getOperand(1));
6584 case Instruction::FPToSI:
6585 case Instruction::FPToUI:
6586 // fptosi/ui yields poison if the resulting value does not fit in the
6587 // destination type.
6588 return true;
6589 case Instruction::Call:
6590 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(Op)) {
6591 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
6592 // TODO: Add more intrinsics.
6593 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
6594 case Intrinsic::cttz:
6595 case Intrinsic::abs:
6596 if (cast<ConstantInt>(II->getArgOperand(1))->isNullValue())
6597 return false;
6598 break;
6599 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
6600 case Intrinsic::bswap:
6601 case Intrinsic::bitreverse:
6602 case Intrinsic::fshl:
6603 case Intrinsic::fshr:
6604 case Intrinsic::smax:
6605 case Intrinsic::smin:
6606 case Intrinsic::umax:
6607 case Intrinsic::umin:
6608 case Intrinsic::ptrmask:
6609 case Intrinsic::fptoui_sat:
6610 case Intrinsic::fptosi_sat:
6611 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
6612 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
6613 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
6614 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
6615 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
6616 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
6617 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
6618 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
6619 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
6620 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
6621 return false;
6622 case Intrinsic::sshl_sat:
6623 case Intrinsic::ushl_sat:
6624 return includesPoison(Kind) &&
6625 !shiftAmountKnownInRange(II->getArgOperand(1));
6626 case Intrinsic::fma:
6627 case Intrinsic::fmuladd:
6628 case Intrinsic::sqrt:
6629 case Intrinsic::powi:
6630 case Intrinsic::sin:
6631 case Intrinsic::cos:
6632 case Intrinsic::pow:
6633 case Intrinsic::log:
6634 case Intrinsic::log10:
6635 case Intrinsic::log2:
6636 case Intrinsic::exp:
6637 case Intrinsic::exp2:
6638 case Intrinsic::exp10:
6639 case Intrinsic::fabs:
6640 case Intrinsic::copysign:
6641 case Intrinsic::floor:
6642 case Intrinsic::ceil:
6643 case Intrinsic::trunc:
6644 case Intrinsic::rint:
6645 case Intrinsic::nearbyint:
6646 case Intrinsic::round:
6647 case Intrinsic::roundeven:
6648 case Intrinsic::fptrunc_round:
6649 case Intrinsic::canonicalize:
6650 case Intrinsic::arithmetic_fence:
6651 case Intrinsic::minnum:
6652 case Intrinsic::maxnum:
6653 case Intrinsic::minimum:
6654 case Intrinsic::maximum:
6655 case Intrinsic::is_fpclass:
6656 case Intrinsic::ldexp:
6657 case Intrinsic::frexp:
6658 return false;
6659 case Intrinsic::lround:
6660 case Intrinsic::llround:
6661 case Intrinsic::lrint:
6662 case Intrinsic::llrint:
6663 // If the value doesn't fit an unspecified value is returned (but this
6664 // is not poison).
6665 return false;
6666 }
6667 }
6668 [[fallthrough]];
6669 case Instruction::CallBr:
6670 case Instruction::Invoke: {
6671 const auto *CB = cast<CallBase>(Op);
6672 return !CB->hasRetAttr(Attribute::NoUndef);
6673 }
6674 case Instruction::InsertElement:
6675 case Instruction::ExtractElement: {
6676 // If index exceeds the length of the vector, it returns poison
6677 auto *VTy = cast<VectorType>(Op->getOperand(0)->getType());
6678 unsigned IdxOp = Op->getOpcode() == Instruction::InsertElement ? 2 : 1;
6679 auto *Idx = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op->getOperand(IdxOp));
6680 if (includesPoison(Kind))
6681 return !Idx ||
6682 Idx->getValue().uge(VTy->getElementCount().getKnownMinValue());
6683 return false;
6684 }
6685 case Instruction::ShuffleVector: {
6686 ArrayRef<int> Mask = isa<ConstantExpr>(Op)
6687 ? cast<ConstantExpr>(Op)->getShuffleMask()
6688 : cast<ShuffleVectorInst>(Op)->getShuffleMask();
6689 return includesPoison(Kind) && is_contained(Mask, PoisonMaskElem);
6690 }
6691 case Instruction::FNeg:
6692 case Instruction::PHI:
6693 case Instruction::Select:
6694 case Instruction::URem:
6695 case Instruction::SRem:
6696 case Instruction::ExtractValue:
6697 case Instruction::InsertValue:
6698 case Instruction::Freeze:
6699 case Instruction::ICmp:
6700 case Instruction::FCmp:
6701 case Instruction::FAdd:
6702 case Instruction::FSub:
6703 case Instruction::FMul:
6704 case Instruction::FDiv:
6705 case Instruction::FRem:
6706 return false;
6707 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
6708 // inbounds is handled above
6709 // TODO: what about inrange on constexpr?
6710 return false;
6711 default: {
6712 const auto *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(Op);
6713 if (isa<CastInst>(Op) || (CE && CE->isCast()))
6714 return false;
6715 else if (Instruction::isBinaryOp(Opcode))
6716 return false;
6717 // Be conservative and return true.
6718 return true;
6719 }
6720 }
6721}
6722
6723bool llvm::canCreateUndefOrPoison(const Operator *Op,
6724 bool ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata) {
6725 return ::canCreateUndefOrPoison(Op, UndefPoisonKind::UndefOrPoison,
6726 ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata);
6727}
6728
6729bool llvm::canCreatePoison(const Operator *Op, bool ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata) {
6730 return ::canCreateUndefOrPoison(Op, UndefPoisonKind::PoisonOnly,
6731 ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata);
6732}
6733
6734static bool directlyImpliesPoison(const Value *ValAssumedPoison, const Value *V,
6735 unsigned Depth) {
6736 if (ValAssumedPoison == V)
6737 return true;
6738
6739 const unsigned MaxDepth = 2;
6740 if (Depth >= MaxDepth)
6741 return false;
6742
6743 if (const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
6744 if (any_of(I->operands(), [=](const Use &Op) {
6745 return propagatesPoison(Op) &&
6746 directlyImpliesPoison(ValAssumedPoison, Op, Depth + 1);
6747 }))
6748 return true;
6749
6750 // V = extractvalue V0, idx
6751 // V2 = extractvalue V0, idx2
6752 // V0's elements are all poison or not. (e.g., add_with_overflow)
6753 const WithOverflowInst *II;
6754 if (match(I, m_ExtractValue(m_WithOverflowInst(II))) &&
6755 (match(ValAssumedPoison, m_ExtractValue(m_Specific(II))) ||
6756 llvm::is_contained(II->args(), ValAssumedPoison)))
6757 return true;
6758 }
6759 return false;
6760}
6761
6762static bool impliesPoison(const Value *ValAssumedPoison, const Value *V,
6763 unsigned Depth) {
6764 if (isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(ValAssumedPoison))
6765 return true;
6766
6767 if (directlyImpliesPoison(ValAssumedPoison, V, /* Depth */ 0))
6768 return true;
6769
6770 const unsigned MaxDepth = 2;
6771 if (Depth >= MaxDepth)
6772 return false;
6773
6774 const auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(ValAssumedPoison);
6775 if (I && !canCreatePoison(cast<Operator>(I))) {
6776 return all_of(I->operands(), [=](const Value *Op) {
6777 return impliesPoison(Op, V, Depth + 1);
6778 });
6779 }
6780 return false;
6781}
6782
6783bool llvm::impliesPoison(const Value *ValAssumedPoison, const Value *V) {
6784 return ::impliesPoison(ValAssumedPoison, V, /* Depth */ 0);
6785}
6786
6787static bool programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Value *V, bool PoisonOnly);
6788
6789static bool isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(
6790 const Value *V, AssumptionCache *AC, const Instruction *CtxI,
6791 const DominatorTree *DT, unsigned Depth, UndefPoisonKind Kind) {
6792 if (Depth >= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
6793 return false;
6794
6795 if (isa<MetadataAsValue>(V))
6796 return false;
6797
6798 if (const auto *A = dyn_cast<Argument>(V)) {
6799 if (A->hasAttribute(Attribute::NoUndef) ||
6800 A->hasAttribute(Attribute::Dereferenceable) ||
6801 A->hasAttribute(Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull))
6802 return true;
6803 }
6804
6805 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V)) {
6806 if (isa<PoisonValue>(C))
6807 return !includesPoison(Kind);
6808
6809 if (isa<UndefValue>(C))
6810 return !includesUndef(Kind);
6811
6812 if (isa<ConstantInt>(C) || isa<GlobalVariable>(C) || isa<ConstantFP>(V) ||
6813 isa<ConstantPointerNull>(C) || isa<Function>(C))
6814 return true;
6815
6816 if (C->getType()->isVectorTy() && !isa<ConstantExpr>(C))
6817 return (!includesUndef(Kind) ? !C->containsPoisonElement()
6818 : !C->containsUndefOrPoisonElement()) &&
6819 !C->containsConstantExpression();
6820 }
6821
6822 // Strip cast operations from a pointer value.
6823 // Note that stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation can strip off getelementptr
6824 // inbounds with zero offset. To guarantee that the result isn't poison, the
6825 // stripped pointer is checked as it has to be pointing into an allocated
6826 // object or be null `null` to ensure `inbounds` getelement pointers with a
6827 // zero offset could not produce poison.
6828 // It can strip off addrspacecast that do not change bit representation as
6829 // well. We believe that such addrspacecast is equivalent to no-op.
6830 auto *StrippedV = V->stripPointerCastsSameRepresentation();
6831 if (isa<AllocaInst>(StrippedV) || isa<GlobalVariable>(StrippedV) ||
6832 isa<Function>(StrippedV) || isa<ConstantPointerNull>(StrippedV))
6833 return true;
6834
6835 auto OpCheck = [&](const Value *V) {
6836 return isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(V, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth + 1, Kind);
6837 };
6838
6839 if (auto *Opr = dyn_cast<Operator>(V)) {
6840 // If the value is a freeze instruction, then it can never
6841 // be undef or poison.
6842 if (isa<FreezeInst>(V))
6843 return true;
6844
6845 if (const auto *CB = dyn_cast<CallBase>(V)) {
6846 if (CB->hasRetAttr(Attribute::NoUndef) ||
6847 CB->hasRetAttr(Attribute::Dereferenceable) ||
6848 CB->hasRetAttr(Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull))
6849 return true;
6850 }
6851
6852 if (const auto *PN = dyn_cast<PHINode>(V)) {
6853 unsigned Num = PN->getNumIncomingValues();
6854 bool IsWellDefined = true;
6855 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Num; ++i) {
6856 auto *TI = PN->getIncomingBlock(i)->getTerminator();
6857 if (!isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(PN->getIncomingValue(i), AC, TI,
6858 DT, Depth + 1, Kind)) {
6859 IsWellDefined = false;
6860 break;
6861 }
6862 }
6863 if (IsWellDefined)
6864 return true;
6865 } else if (!::canCreateUndefOrPoison(Opr, Kind,
6866 /*ConsiderFlagsAndMetadata*/ true) &&
6867 all_of(Opr->operands(), OpCheck))
6868 return true;
6869 }
6870
6871 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<LoadInst>(V))
6872 if (I->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_noundef) ||
6873 I->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable) ||
6874 I->hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_dereferenceable_or_null))
6875 return true;
6876
6877 if (programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(V, !includesUndef(Kind)))
6878 return true;
6879
6880 // CxtI may be null or a cloned instruction.
6881 if (!CtxI || !CtxI->getParent() || !DT)
6882 return false;
6883
6884 auto *DNode = DT->getNode(CtxI->getParent());
6885 if (!DNode)
6886 // Unreachable block
6887 return false;
6888
6889 // If V is used as a branch condition before reaching CtxI, V cannot be
6890 // undef or poison.
6891 // br V, BB1, BB2
6892 // BB1:
6893 // CtxI ; V cannot be undef or poison here
6894 auto *Dominator = DNode->getIDom();
6895 while (Dominator) {
6896 auto *TI = Dominator->getBlock()->getTerminator();
6897
6898 Value *Cond = nullptr;
6899 if (auto BI = dyn_cast_or_null<BranchInst>(TI)) {
6900 if (BI->isConditional())
6901 Cond = BI->getCondition();
6902 } else if (auto SI = dyn_cast_or_null<SwitchInst>(TI)) {
6903 Cond = SI->getCondition();
6904 }
6905
6906 if (Cond) {
6907 if (Cond == V)
6908 return true;
6909 else if (!includesUndef(Kind) && isa<Operator>(Cond)) {
6910 // For poison, we can analyze further
6911 auto *Opr = cast<Operator>(Cond);
6912 if (any_of(Opr->operands(),
6913 [V](const Use &U) { return V == U && propagatesPoison(U); }))
6914 return true;
6915 }
6916 }
6917
6918 Dominator = Dominator->getIDom();
6919 }
6920
6921 if (getKnowledgeValidInContext(V, {Attribute::NoUndef}, CtxI, DT, AC))
6922 return true;
6923
6924 return false;
6925}
6926
6927bool llvm::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(const Value *V, AssumptionCache *AC,
6928 const Instruction *CtxI,
6929 const DominatorTree *DT,
6930 unsigned Depth) {
6931 return ::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(V, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth,
6932 UndefPoisonKind::UndefOrPoison);
6933}
6934
6935bool llvm::isGuaranteedNotToBePoison(const Value *V, AssumptionCache *AC,
6936 const Instruction *CtxI,
6937 const DominatorTree *DT, unsigned Depth) {
6938 return ::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(V, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth,
6939 UndefPoisonKind::PoisonOnly);
6940}
6941
6942bool llvm::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndef(const Value *V, AssumptionCache *AC,
6943 const Instruction *CtxI,
6944 const DominatorTree *DT, unsigned Depth) {
6945 return ::isGuaranteedNotToBeUndefOrPoison(V, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth,
6946 UndefPoisonKind::UndefOnly);
6947}
6948
6949/// Return true if undefined behavior would provably be executed on the path to
6950/// OnPathTo if Root produced a posion result. Note that this doesn't say
6951/// anything about whether OnPathTo is actually executed or whether Root is
6952/// actually poison. This can be used to assess whether a new use of Root can
6953/// be added at a location which is control equivalent with OnPathTo (such as
6954/// immediately before it) without introducing UB which didn't previously
6955/// exist. Note that a false result conveys no information.
6956bool llvm::mustExecuteUBIfPoisonOnPathTo(Instruction *Root,
6957 Instruction *OnPathTo,
6958 DominatorTree *DT) {
6959 // Basic approach is to assume Root is poison, propagate poison forward
6960 // through all users we can easily track, and then check whether any of those
6961 // users are provable UB and must execute before out exiting block might
6962 // exit.
6963
6964 // The set of all recursive users we've visited (which are assumed to all be
6965 // poison because of said visit)
6966 SmallSet<const Value *, 16> KnownPoison;
6967 SmallVector<const Instruction*, 16> Worklist;
6968 Worklist.push_back(Root);
6969 while (!Worklist.empty()) {
6970 const Instruction *I = Worklist.pop_back_val();
6971
6972 // If we know this must trigger UB on a path leading our target.
6973 if (mustTriggerUB(I, KnownPoison) && DT->dominates(I, OnPathTo))
6974 return true;
6975
6976 // If we can't analyze propagation through this instruction, just skip it
6977 // and transitive users. Safe as false is a conservative result.
6978 if (I != Root && !any_of(I->operands(), [&KnownPoison](const Use &U) {
6979 return KnownPoison.contains(U) && propagatesPoison(U);
6980 }))
6981 continue;
6982
6983 if (KnownPoison.insert(I).second)
6984 for (const User *User : I->users())
6985 Worklist.push_back(cast<Instruction>(User));
6986 }
6987
6988 // Might be non-UB, or might have a path we couldn't prove must execute on
6989 // way to exiting bb.
6990 return false;
6991}
6992
6993OverflowResult llvm::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(const AddOperator *Add,
6994 const SimplifyQuery &SQ) {
6995 return ::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(Add->getOperand(0), Add->getOperand(1),
6996 Add, SQ);
6997}
6998
6999OverflowResult
7000llvm::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(const WithCache<const Value *> &LHS,
7001 const WithCache<const Value *> &RHS,
7002 const SimplifyQuery &SQ) {
7003 return ::computeOverflowForSignedAdd(LHS, RHS, nullptr, SQ);
7004}
7005
7006bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const Instruction *I) {
7007 // Note: An atomic operation isn't guaranteed to return in a reasonable amount
7008 // of time because it's possible for another thread to interfere with it for an
7009 // arbitrary length of time, but programs aren't allowed to rely on that.
7010
7011 // If there is no successor, then execution can't transfer to it.
7012 if (isa<ReturnInst>(I))
7013 return false;
7014 if (isa<UnreachableInst>(I))
7015 return false;
7016
7017 // Note: Do not add new checks here; instead, change Instruction::mayThrow or
7018 // Instruction::willReturn.
7019 //
7020 // FIXME: Move this check into Instruction::willReturn.
7021 if (isa<CatchPadInst>(I)) {
7022 switch (classifyEHPersonality(I->getFunction()->getPersonalityFn())) {
7023 default:
7024 // A catchpad may invoke exception object constructors and such, which
7025 // in some languages can be arbitrary code, so be conservative by default.
7026 return false;
7027 case EHPersonality::CoreCLR:
7028 // For CoreCLR, it just involves a type test.
7029 return true;
7030 }
7031 }
7032
7033 // An instruction that returns without throwing must transfer control flow
7034 // to a successor.
7035 return !I->mayThrow() && I->willReturn();
7036}
7037
7038bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(const BasicBlock *BB) {
7039 // TODO: This is slightly conservative for invoke instruction since exiting
7040 // via an exception *is* normal control for them.
7041 for (const Instruction &I : *BB)
7042 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
7043 return false;
7044 return true;
7045}
7046
7047bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(
7048 BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin, BasicBlock::const_iterator End,
7049 unsigned ScanLimit) {
7050 return isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(make_range(Begin, End),
7051 ScanLimit);
7052}
7053
7054bool llvm::isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(
7055 iterator_range<BasicBlock::const_iterator> Range, unsigned ScanLimit) {
7056 assert(ScanLimit && "scan limit must be non-zero");
7057 for (const Instruction &I : Range) {
7058 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
7059 continue;
7060 if (--ScanLimit == 0)
7061 return false;
7062 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
7063 return false;
7064 }
7065 return true;
7066}
7067
7068bool llvm::isGuaranteedToExecuteForEveryIteration(const Instruction *I,
7069 const Loop *L) {
7070 // The loop header is guaranteed to be executed for every iteration.
7071 //
7072 // FIXME: Relax this constraint to cover all basic blocks that are
7073 // guaranteed to be executed at every iteration.
7074 if (I->getParent() != L->getHeader()) return false;
7075
7076 for (const Instruction &LI : *L->getHeader()) {
7077 if (&LI == I) return true;
7078 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&LI)) return false;
7079 }
7080 llvm_unreachable("Instruction not contained in its own parent basic block.");
7081}
7082
7083bool llvm::propagatesPoison(const Use &PoisonOp) {
7084 const Operator *I = cast<Operator>(PoisonOp.getUser());
7085 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
7086 case Instruction::Freeze:
7087 case Instruction::PHI:
7088 case Instruction::Invoke:
7089 return false;
7090 case Instruction::Select:
7091 return PoisonOp.getOperandNo() == 0;
7092 case Instruction::Call:
7093 if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(I)) {
7094 switch (II->getIntrinsicID()) {
7095 // TODO: Add more intrinsics.
7096 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
7097 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
7098 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
7099 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
7100 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
7101 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
7102 // If an input is a vector containing a poison element, the
7103 // two output vectors (calculated results, overflow bits)'
7104 // corresponding lanes are poison.
7105 return true;
7106 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
7107 return true;
7108 }
7109 }
7110 return false;
7111 case Instruction::ICmp:
7112 case Instruction::FCmp:
7113 case Instruction::GetElementPtr:
7114 return true;
7115 default:
7116 if (isa<BinaryOperator>(I) || isa<UnaryOperator>(I) || isa<CastInst>(I))
7117 return true;
7118
7119 // Be conservative and return false.
7120 return false;
7121 }
7122}
7123
7124void llvm::getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(
7125 const Instruction *I, SmallVectorImpl<const Value *> &Operands) {
7126 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
7127 case Instruction::Store:
7128 Operands.push_back(cast<StoreInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
7129 break;
7130
7131 case Instruction::Load:
7132 Operands.push_back(cast<LoadInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
7133 break;
7134
7135 // Since dereferenceable attribute imply noundef, atomic operations
7136 // also implicitly have noundef pointers too
7137 case Instruction::AtomicCmpXchg:
7138 Operands.push_back(cast<AtomicCmpXchgInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
7139 break;
7140
7141 case Instruction::AtomicRMW:
7142 Operands.push_back(cast<AtomicRMWInst>(I)->getPointerOperand());
7143 break;
7144
7145 case Instruction::Call:
7146 case Instruction::Invoke: {
7147 const CallBase *CB = cast<CallBase>(I);
7148 if (CB->isIndirectCall())
7149 Operands.push_back(CB->getCalledOperand());
7150 for (unsigned i = 0; i < CB->arg_size(); ++i) {
7151 if (CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::NoUndef) ||
7152 CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::Dereferenceable) ||
7153 CB->paramHasAttr(i, Attribute::DereferenceableOrNull))
7154 Operands.push_back(CB->getArgOperand(i));
7155 }
7156 break;
7157 }
7158 case Instruction::Ret:
7159 if (I->getFunction()->hasRetAttribute(Attribute::NoUndef))
7160 Operands.push_back(I->getOperand(0));
7161 break;
7162 case Instruction::Switch:
7163 Operands.push_back(cast<SwitchInst>(I)->getCondition());
7164 break;
7165 case Instruction::Br: {
7166 auto *BR = cast<BranchInst>(I);
7167 if (BR->isConditional())
7168 Operands.push_back(BR->getCondition());
7169 break;
7170 }
7171 default:
7172 break;
7173 }
7174}
7175
7176void llvm::getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(const Instruction *I,
7177 SmallVectorImpl<const Value *> &Operands) {
7178 getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(I, Operands);
7179 switch (I->getOpcode()) {
7180 // Divisors of these operations are allowed to be partially undef.
7181 case Instruction::UDiv:
7182 case Instruction::SDiv:
7183 case Instruction::URem:
7184 case Instruction::SRem:
7185 Operands.push_back(I->getOperand(1));
7186 break;
7187 default:
7188 break;
7189 }
7190}
7191
7192bool llvm::mustTriggerUB(const Instruction *I,
7193 const SmallPtrSetImpl<const Value *> &KnownPoison) {
7194 SmallVector<const Value *, 4> NonPoisonOps;
7195 getGuaranteedNonPoisonOps(I, NonPoisonOps);
7196
7197 for (const auto *V : NonPoisonOps)
7198 if (KnownPoison.count(V))
7199 return true;
7200
7201 return false;
7202}
7203
7204static bool programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Value *V,
7205 bool PoisonOnly) {
7206 // We currently only look for uses of values within the same basic
7207 // block, as that makes it easier to guarantee that the uses will be
7208 // executed given that Inst is executed.
7209 //
7210 // FIXME: Expand this to consider uses beyond the same basic block. To do
7211 // this, look out for the distinction between post-dominance and strong
7212 // post-dominance.
7213 const BasicBlock *BB = nullptr;
7214 BasicBlock::const_iterator Begin;
7215 if (const auto *Inst = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V)) {
7216 BB = Inst->getParent();
7217 Begin = Inst->getIterator();
7218 Begin++;
7219 } else if (const auto *Arg = dyn_cast<Argument>(V)) {
7220 if (Arg->getParent()->isDeclaration())
7221 return false;
7222 BB = &Arg->getParent()->getEntryBlock();
7223 Begin = BB->begin();
7224 } else {
7225 return false;
7226 }
7227
7228 // Limit number of instructions we look at, to avoid scanning through large
7229 // blocks. The current limit is chosen arbitrarily.
7230 unsigned ScanLimit = 32;
7231 BasicBlock::const_iterator End = BB->end();
7232
7233 if (!PoisonOnly) {
7234 // Since undef does not propagate eagerly, be conservative & just check
7235 // whether a value is directly passed to an instruction that must take
7236 // well-defined operands.
7237
7238 for (const auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
7239 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
7240 continue;
7241 if (--ScanLimit == 0)
7242 break;
7243
7244 SmallVector<const Value *, 4> WellDefinedOps;
7245 getGuaranteedWellDefinedOps(&I, WellDefinedOps);
7246 if (is_contained(WellDefinedOps, V))
7247 return true;
7248
7249 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
7250 break;
7251 }
7252 return false;
7253 }
7254
7255 // Set of instructions that we have proved will yield poison if Inst
7256 // does.
7257 SmallSet<const Value *, 16> YieldsPoison;
7258 SmallSet<const BasicBlock *, 4> Visited;
7259
7260 YieldsPoison.insert(V);
7261 Visited.insert(BB);
7262
7263 while (true) {
7264 for (const auto &I : make_range(Begin, End)) {
7265 if (isa<DbgInfoIntrinsic>(I))
7266 continue;
7267 if (--ScanLimit == 0)
7268 return false;
7269 if (mustTriggerUB(&I, YieldsPoison))
7270 return true;
7271 if (!isGuaranteedToTransferExecutionToSuccessor(&I))
7272 return false;
7273
7274 // If an operand is poison and propagates it, mark I as yielding poison.
7275 for (const Use &Op : I.operands()) {
7276 if (YieldsPoison.count(Op) && propagatesPoison(Op)) {
7277 YieldsPoison.insert(&I);
7278 break;
7279 }
7280 }
7281
7282 // Special handling for select, which returns poison if its operand 0 is
7283 // poison (handled in the loop above) *or* if both its true/false operands
7284 // are poison (handled here).
7285 if (I.getOpcode() == Instruction::Select &&
7286 YieldsPoison.count(I.getOperand(1)) &&
7287 YieldsPoison.count(I.getOperand(2))) {
7288 YieldsPoison.insert(&I);
7289 }
7290 }
7291
7292 BB = BB->getSingleSuccessor();
7293 if (!BB || !Visited.insert(BB).second)
7294 break;
7295
7296 Begin = BB->getFirstNonPHI()->getIterator();
7297 End = BB->end();
7298 }
7299 return false;
7300}
7301
7302bool llvm::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
7303 return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, false);
7304}
7305
7306bool llvm::programUndefinedIfPoison(const Instruction *Inst) {
7307 return ::programUndefinedIfUndefOrPoison(Inst, true);
7308}
7309
7310static bool isKnownNonNaN(const Value *V, FastMathFlags FMF) {
7311 if (FMF.noNaNs())
7312 return true;
7313
7314 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
7315 return !C->isNaN();
7316
7317 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
7318 if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
7319 return false;
7320 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
7321 if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isNaN())
7322 return false;
7323 }
7324 return true;
7325 }
7326
7327 if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(V))
7328 return true;
7329
7330 return false;
7331}
7332
7333static bool isKnownNonZero(const Value *V) {
7334 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(V))
7335 return !C->isZero();
7336
7337 if (auto *C = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
7338 if (!C->getElementType()->isFloatingPointTy())
7339 return false;
7340 for (unsigned I = 0, E = C->getNumElements(); I < E; ++I) {
7341 if (C->getElementAsAPFloat(I).isZero())
7342 return false;
7343 }
7344 return true;
7345 }
7346
7347 return false;
7348}
7349
7350/// Match clamp pattern for float types without care about NaNs or signed zeros.
7351/// Given non-min/max outer cmp/select from the clamp pattern this
7352/// function recognizes if it can be substitued by a "canonical" min/max
7353/// pattern.
7354static SelectPatternResult matchFastFloatClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7355 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
7356 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
7357 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS) {
7358 // Try to match
7359 // X < C1 ? C1 : Min(X, C2) --> Max(C1, Min(X, C2))
7360 // X > C1 ? C1 : Max(X, C2) --> Min(C1, Max(X, C2))
7361 // and return description of the outer Max/Min.
7362
7363 // First, check if select has inverse order:
7364 if (CmpRHS == FalseVal) {
7365 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
7366 Pred = CmpInst::getInversePredicate(Pred);
7367 }
7368
7369 // Assume success now. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
7370 LHS = TrueVal;
7371 RHS = FalseVal;
7372
7373 const APFloat *FC1;
7374 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal || !match(CmpRHS, m_APFloat(FC1)) || !FC1->isFinite())
7375 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7376
7377 const APFloat *FC2;
7378 switch (Pred) {
7379 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
7380 case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
7381 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
7382 case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
7383 if (match(FalseVal,
7384 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
7385 m_UnordFMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
7386 *FC1 < *FC2)
7387 return {SPF_FMAXNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
7388 break;
7389 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
7390 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE:
7391 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
7392 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
7393 if (match(FalseVal,
7394 m_CombineOr(m_OrdFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)),
7395 m_UnordFMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APFloat(FC2)))) &&
7396 *FC1 > *FC2)
7397 return {SPF_FMINNUM, SPNB_RETURNS_ANY, false};
7398 break;
7399 default:
7400 break;
7401 }
7402
7403 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7404}
7405
7406/// Recognize variations of:
7407/// CLAMP(v,l,h) ==> ((v) < (l) ? (l) : ((v) > (h) ? (h) : (v)))
7408static SelectPatternResult matchClamp(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7409 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
7410 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal) {
7411 // Swap the select operands and predicate to match the patterns below.
7412 if (CmpRHS != TrueVal) {
7413 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7414 std::swap(TrueVal, FalseVal);
7415 }
7416 const APInt *C1;
7417 if (CmpRHS == TrueVal && match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1))) {
7418 const APInt *C2;
7419 // (X <s C1) ? C1 : SMIN(X, C2) ==> SMAX(SMIN(X, C2), C1)
7420 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
7421 C1->slt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
7422 return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7423
7424 // (X >s C1) ? C1 : SMAX(X, C2) ==> SMIN(SMAX(X, C2), C1)
7425 if (match(FalseVal, m_SMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
7426 C1->sgt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT)
7427 return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7428
7429 // (X <u C1) ? C1 : UMIN(X, C2) ==> UMAX(UMIN(X, C2), C1)
7430 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMin(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
7431 C1->ult(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_ULT)
7432 return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7433
7434 // (X >u C1) ? C1 : UMAX(X, C2) ==> UMIN(UMAX(X, C2), C1)
7435 if (match(FalseVal, m_UMax(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_APInt(C2))) &&
7436 C1->ugt(*C2) && Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_UGT)
7437 return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7438 }
7439 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7440}
7441
7442/// Recognize variations of:
7443/// a < c ? min(a,b) : min(b,c) ==> min(min(a,b),min(b,c))
7444static SelectPatternResult matchMinMaxOfMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7445 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
7446 Value *TVal, Value *FVal,
7447 unsigned Depth) {
7448 // TODO: Allow FP min/max with nnan/nsz.
7449 assert(CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred) && "Expected integer comparison");
7450
7451 Value *A = nullptr, *B = nullptr;
7452 SelectPatternResult L = matchSelectPattern(TVal, A, B, nullptr, Depth + 1);
7453 if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(L.Flavor))
7454 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7455
7456 Value *C = nullptr, *D = nullptr;
7457 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(FVal, C, D, nullptr, Depth + 1);
7458 if (L.Flavor != R.Flavor)
7459 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7460
7461 // We have something like: x Pred y ? min(a, b) : min(c, d).
7462 // Try to match the compare to the min/max operations of the select operands.
7463 // First, make sure we have the right compare predicate.
7464 switch (L.Flavor) {
7465 case SPF_SMIN:
7466 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE) {
7467 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7468 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
7469 }
7470 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE)
7471 break;
7472 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7473 case SPF_SMAX:
7474 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE) {
7475 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7476 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
7477 }
7478 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE)
7479 break;
7480 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7481 case SPF_UMIN:
7482 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) {
7483 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7484 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
7485 }
7486 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE)
7487 break;
7488 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7489 case SPF_UMAX:
7490 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE) {
7491 Pred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7492 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
7493 }
7494 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT || Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE)
7495 break;
7496 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7497 default:
7498 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7499 }
7500
7501 // If there is a common operand in the already matched min/max and the other
7502 // min/max operands match the compare operands (either directly or inverted),
7503 // then this is min/max of the same flavor.
7504
7505 // a pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
7506 // ~c pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(c, b) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, b))
7507 if (D == B) {
7508 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
7509 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
7510 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
7511 }
7512 // a pred d ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
7513 // ~d pred ~a ? m(a, b) : m(b, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(b, d))
7514 if (C == B) {
7515 if ((CmpLHS == A && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
7516 match(A, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
7517 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
7518 }
7519 // b pred c ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
7520 // ~c pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(c, a) --> m(m(a, b), m(c, a))
7521 if (D == A) {
7522 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == C) || (match(C, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
7523 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
7524 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
7525 }
7526 // b pred d ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
7527 // ~d pred ~b ? m(a, b) : m(a, d) --> m(m(a, b), m(a, d))
7528 if (C == A) {
7529 if ((CmpLHS == B && CmpRHS == D) || (match(D, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpLHS))) &&
7530 match(B, m_Not(m_Specific(CmpRHS)))))
7531 return {L.Flavor, SPNB_NA, false};
7532 }
7533
7534 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7535}
7536
7537/// If the input value is the result of a 'not' op, constant integer, or vector
7538/// splat of a constant integer, return the bitwise-not source value.
7539/// TODO: This could be extended to handle non-splat vector integer constants.
7540static Value *getNotValue(Value *V) {
7541 Value *NotV;
7542 if (match(V, m_Not(m_Value(NotV))))
7543 return NotV;
7544
7545 const APInt *C;
7546 if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
7547 return ConstantInt::get(V->getType(), ~(*C));
7548
7549 return nullptr;
7550}
7551
7552/// Match non-obvious integer minimum and maximum sequences.
7553static SelectPatternResult matchMinMax(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7554 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
7555 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
7556 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
7557 unsigned Depth) {
7558 // Assume success. If there's no match, callers should not use these anyway.
7559 LHS = TrueVal;
7560 RHS = FalseVal;
7561
7562 SelectPatternResult SPR = matchClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal);
7563 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
7564 return SPR;
7565
7566 SPR = matchMinMaxOfMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, Depth);
7567 if (SPR.Flavor != SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_UNKNOWN)
7568 return SPR;
7569
7570 // Look through 'not' ops to find disguised min/max.
7571 // (X > Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MIN(~X, ~Y)
7572 // (X < Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~X : ~Y ==> MAX(~X, ~Y)
7573 if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(TrueVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(FalseVal)) {
7574 switch (Pred) {
7575 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7576 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7577 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7578 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7579 default: break;
7580 }
7581 }
7582
7583 // (X > Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X < ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MAX(~Y, ~X)
7584 // (X < Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> (~X > ~Y) ? ~Y : ~X ==> MIN(~Y, ~X)
7585 if (CmpLHS == getNotValue(FalseVal) && CmpRHS == getNotValue(TrueVal)) {
7586 switch (Pred) {
7587 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7588 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7589 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7590 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7591 default: break;
7592 }
7593 }
7594
7595 if (Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && Pred != CmpInst::ICMP_SLT)
7596 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7597
7598 const APInt *C1;
7599 if (!match(CmpRHS, m_APInt(C1)))
7600 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7601
7602 // An unsigned min/max can be written with a signed compare.
7603 const APInt *C2;
7604 if ((CmpLHS == TrueVal && match(FalseVal, m_APInt(C2))) ||
7605 (CmpLHS == FalseVal && match(TrueVal, m_APInt(C2)))) {
7606 // Is the sign bit set?
7607 // (X <s 0) ? X : MAXVAL ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? X : MAXVAL ==> UMAX
7608 // (X <s 0) ? MAXVAL : X ==> (X >u MAXVAL) ? MAXVAL : X ==> UMIN
7609 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SLT && C1->isZero() && C2->isMaxSignedValue())
7610 return {CmpLHS == TrueVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7611
7612 // Is the sign bit clear?
7613 // (X >s -1) ? MINVAL : X ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? MINVAL : X ==> UMAX
7614 // (X >s -1) ? X : MINVAL ==> (X <u MINVAL) ? X : MINVAL ==> UMIN
7615 if (Pred == CmpInst::ICMP_SGT && C1->isAllOnes() && C2->isMinSignedValue())
7616 return {CmpLHS == FalseVal ? SPF_UMAX : SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7617 }
7618
7619 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7620}
7621
7622bool llvm::isKnownNegation(const Value *X, const Value *Y, bool NeedNSW) {
7623 assert(X && Y && "Invalid operand");
7624
7625 // X = sub (0, Y) || X = sub nsw (0, Y)
7626 if ((!NeedNSW && match(X, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))) ||
7627 (NeedNSW && match(X, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(Y)))))
7628 return true;
7629
7630 // Y = sub (0, X) || Y = sub nsw (0, X)
7631 if ((!NeedNSW && match(Y, m_Sub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))) ||
7632 (NeedNSW && match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_ZeroInt(), m_Specific(X)))))
7633 return true;
7634
7635 // X = sub (A, B), Y = sub (B, A) || X = sub nsw (A, B), Y = sub nsw (B, A)
7636 Value *A, *B;
7637 return (!NeedNSW && (match(X, m_Sub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
7638 match(Y, m_Sub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A))))) ||
7639 (NeedNSW && (match(X, m_NSWSub(m_Value(A), m_Value(B))) &&
7640 match(Y, m_NSWSub(m_Specific(B), m_Specific(A)))));
7641}
7642
7643static SelectPatternResult matchSelectPattern(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
7644 FastMathFlags FMF,
7645 Value *CmpLHS, Value *CmpRHS,
7646 Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal,
7647 Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
7648 unsigned Depth) {
7649 bool HasMismatchedZeros = false;
7650 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
7651 // IEEE-754 ignores the sign of 0.0 in comparisons. So if the select has one
7652 // 0.0 operand, set the compare's 0.0 operands to that same value for the
7653 // purpose of identifying min/max. Disregard vector constants with undefined
7654 // elements because those can not be back-propagated for analysis.
7655 Value *OutputZeroVal = nullptr;
7656 if (match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
7657 !cast<Constant>(TrueVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
7658 OutputZeroVal = TrueVal;
7659 else if (match(FalseVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) && !match(TrueVal, m_AnyZeroFP()) &&
7660 !cast<Constant>(FalseVal)->containsUndefOrPoisonElement())
7661 OutputZeroVal = FalseVal;
7662
7663 if (OutputZeroVal) {
7664 if (match(CmpLHS, m_AnyZeroFP()) && CmpLHS != OutputZeroVal) {
7665 HasMismatchedZeros = true;
7666 CmpLHS = OutputZeroVal;
7667 }
7668 if (match(CmpRHS, m_AnyZeroFP()) && CmpRHS != OutputZeroVal) {
7669 HasMismatchedZeros = true;
7670 CmpRHS = OutputZeroVal;
7671 }
7672 }
7673 }
7674
7675 LHS = CmpLHS;
7676 RHS = CmpRHS;
7677
7678 // Signed zero may return inconsistent results between implementations.
7679 // (0.0 <= -0.0) ? 0.0 : -0.0 // Returns 0.0
7680 // minNum(0.0, -0.0) // May return -0.0 or 0.0 (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1)
7681 // Therefore, we behave conservatively and only proceed if at least one of the
7682 // operands is known to not be zero or if we don't care about signed zero.
7683 switch (Pred) {
7684 default: break;
7685 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGT: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
7686 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGT: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
7687 if (!HasMismatchedZeros)
7688 break;
7689 [[fallthrough]];
7690 case CmpInst::FCMP_OGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_OLE:
7691 case CmpInst::FCMP_UGE: case CmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
7692 if (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
7693 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS))
7694 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7695 }
7696
7697 SelectPatternNaNBehavior NaNBehavior = SPNB_NA;
7698 bool Ordered = false;
7699
7700 // When given one NaN and one non-NaN input:
7701 // - maxnum/minnum (C99 fmaxf()/fminf()) return the non-NaN input.
7702 // - A simple C99 (a < b ? a : b) construction will return 'b' (as the
7703 // ordered comparison fails), which could be NaN or non-NaN.
7704 // so here we discover exactly what NaN behavior is required/accepted.
7705 if (CmpInst::isFPPredicate(Pred)) {
7706 bool LHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpLHS, FMF);
7707 bool RHSSafe = isKnownNonNaN(CmpRHS, FMF);
7708
7709 if (LHSSafe && RHSSafe) {
7710 // Both operands are known non-NaN.
7711 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_ANY;
7712 } else if (CmpInst::isOrdered(Pred)) {
7713 // An ordered comparison will return false when given a NaN, so it
7714 // returns the RHS.
7715 Ordered = true;
7716 if (LHSSafe)
7717 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then NaN will be returned.
7718 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
7719 else if (RHSSafe)
7720 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
7721 else
7722 // Completely unsafe.
7723 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7724 } else {
7725 Ordered = false;
7726 // An unordered comparison will return true when given a NaN, so it
7727 // returns the LHS.
7728 if (LHSSafe)
7729 // LHS is non-NaN, so if RHS is NaN then non-NaN will be returned.
7730 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
7731 else if (RHSSafe)
7732 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
7733 else
7734 // Completely unsafe.
7735 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7736 }
7737 }
7738
7739 if (TrueVal == CmpRHS && FalseVal == CmpLHS) {
7740 std::swap(CmpLHS, CmpRHS);
7741 Pred = CmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(Pred);
7742 if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_NAN)
7743 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER;
7744 else if (NaNBehavior == SPNB_RETURNS_OTHER)
7745 NaNBehavior = SPNB_RETURNS_NAN;
7746 Ordered = !Ordered;
7747 }
7748
7749 // ([if]cmp X, Y) ? X : Y
7750 if (TrueVal == CmpLHS && FalseVal == CmpRHS) {
7751 switch (Pred) {
7752 default: return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false}; // Equality.
7753 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
7754 case ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE: return {SPF_UMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7755 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
7756 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE: return {SPF_SMAX, SPNB_NA, false};
7757 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
7758 case ICmpInst::ICMP_ULE: return {SPF_UMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7759 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
7760 case ICmpInst::ICMP_SLE: return {SPF_SMIN, SPNB_NA, false};
7761 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT:
7762 case FCmpInst::FCMP_UGE:
7763 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT:
7764 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OGE: return {SPF_FMAXNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
7765 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT:
7766 case FCmpInst::FCMP_ULE:
7767 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT:
7768 case FCmpInst::FCMP_OLE: return {SPF_FMINNUM, NaNBehavior, Ordered};
7769 }
7770 }
7771
7772 if (isKnownNegation(TrueVal, FalseVal)) {
7773 // Sign-extending LHS does not change its sign, so TrueVal/FalseVal can
7774 // match against either LHS or sext(LHS).
7775 auto MaybeSExtCmpLHS =
7776 m_CombineOr(m_Specific(CmpLHS), m_SExt(m_Specific(CmpLHS)));
7777 auto ZeroOrAllOnes = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_AllOnes());
7778 auto ZeroOrOne = m_CombineOr(m_ZeroInt(), m_One());
7779 if (match(TrueVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
7780 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
7781 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
7782 LHS = TrueVal;
7783 RHS = FalseVal;
7784 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(FalseVal))))
7785 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
7786
7787 // (X >s 0) ? X : -X or (X >s -1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
7788 // (-X >s 0) ? -X : X or (-X >s -1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
7789 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
7790 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
7791
7792 // (X >=s 0) ? X : -X or (X >=s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
7793 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGE && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
7794 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
7795
7796 // (X <s 0) ? X : -X or (X <s 1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
7797 // (-X <s 0) ? -X : X or (-X <s 1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
7798 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
7799 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
7800 }
7801 else if (match(FalseVal, MaybeSExtCmpLHS)) {
7802 // Set the return values. If the compare uses the negated value (-X >s 0),
7803 // swap the return values because the negated value is always 'RHS'.
7804 LHS = FalseVal;
7805 RHS = TrueVal;
7806 if (match(CmpLHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(TrueVal))))
7807 std::swap(LHS, RHS);
7808
7809 // (X >s 0) ? -X : X or (X >s -1) ? -X : X --> NABS(X)
7810 // (-X >s 0) ? X : -X or (-X >s -1) ? X : -X --> NABS(X)
7811 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrAllOnes))
7812 return {SPF_NABS, SPNB_NA, false};
7813
7814 // (X <s 0) ? -X : X or (X <s 1) ? -X : X --> ABS(X)
7815 // (-X <s 0) ? X : -X or (-X <s 1) ? X : -X --> ABS(X)
7816 if (Pred == ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT && match(CmpRHS, ZeroOrOne))
7817 return {SPF_ABS, SPNB_NA, false};
7818 }
7819 }
7820
7821 if (CmpInst::isIntPredicate(Pred))
7822 return matchMinMax(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS, Depth);
7823
7824 // According to (IEEE 754-2008 5.3.1), minNum(0.0, -0.0) and similar
7825 // may return either -0.0 or 0.0, so fcmp/select pair has stricter
7826 // semantics than minNum. Be conservative in such case.
7827 if (NaNBehavior != SPNB_RETURNS_ANY ||
7828 (!FMF.noSignedZeros() && !isKnownNonZero(CmpLHS) &&
7829 !isKnownNonZero(CmpRHS)))
7830 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7831
7832 return matchFastFloatClamp(Pred, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS);
7833}
7834
7835/// Helps to match a select pattern in case of a type mismatch.
7836///
7837/// The function processes the case when type of true and false values of a
7838/// select instruction differs from type of the cmp instruction operands because
7839/// of a cast instruction. The function checks if it is legal to move the cast
7840/// operation after "select". If yes, it returns the new second value of
7841/// "select" (with the assumption that cast is moved):
7842/// 1. As operand of cast instruction when both values of "select" are same cast
7843/// instructions.
7844/// 2. As restored constant (by applying reverse cast operation) when the first
7845/// value of the "select" is a cast operation and the second value is a
7846/// constant.
7847/// NOTE: We return only the new second value because the first value could be
7848/// accessed as operand of cast instruction.
7849static Value *lookThroughCast(CmpInst *CmpI, Value *V1, Value *V2,
7850 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp) {
7851 auto *Cast1 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V1);
7852 if (!Cast1)
7853 return nullptr;
7854
7855 *CastOp = Cast1->getOpcode();
7856 Type *SrcTy = Cast1->getSrcTy();
7857 if (auto *Cast2 = dyn_cast<CastInst>(V2)) {
7858 // If V1 and V2 are both the same cast from the same type, look through V1.
7859 if (*CastOp == Cast2->getOpcode() && SrcTy == Cast2->getSrcTy())
7860 return Cast2->getOperand(0);
7861 return nullptr;
7862 }
7863
7864 auto *C = dyn_cast<Constant>(V2);
7865 if (!C)
7866 return nullptr;
7867
7868 const DataLayout &DL = CmpI->getModule()->getDataLayout();
7869 Constant *CastedTo = nullptr;
7870 switch (*CastOp) {
7871 case Instruction::ZExt:
7872 if (CmpI->isUnsigned())
7873 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy);
7874 break;
7875 case Instruction::SExt:
7876 if (CmpI->isSigned())
7877 CastedTo = ConstantExpr::getTrunc(C, SrcTy, true);
7878 break;
7879 case Instruction::Trunc:
7880 Constant *CmpConst;
7881 if (match(CmpI->getOperand(1), m_Constant(CmpConst)) &&
7882 CmpConst->getType() == SrcTy) {
7883 // Here we have the following case:
7884 //
7885 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
7886 // %tr = trunc iN %x to iK
7887 // %narrowsel = select i1 %cond, iK %t, iK C
7888 //
7889 // We can always move trunc after select operation:
7890 //
7891 // %cond = cmp iN %x, CmpConst
7892 // %widesel = select i1 %cond, iN %x, iN CmpConst
7893 // %tr = trunc iN %widesel to iK
7894 //
7895 // Note that C could be extended in any way because we don't care about
7896 // upper bits after truncation. It can't be abs pattern, because it would
7897 // look like:
7898 //
7899 // select i1 %cond, x, -x.
7900 //
7901 // So only min/max pattern could be matched. Such match requires widened C
7902 // == CmpConst. That is why set widened C = CmpConst, condition trunc
7903 // CmpConst == C is checked below.
7904 CastedTo = CmpConst;
7905 } else {
7906 unsigned ExtOp = CmpI->isSigned() ? Instruction::SExt : Instruction::ZExt;
7907 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(ExtOp, C, SrcTy, DL);
7908 }
7909 break;
7910 case Instruction::FPTrunc:
7911 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::FPExt, C, SrcTy, DL);
7912 break;
7913 case Instruction::FPExt:
7914 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::FPTrunc, C, SrcTy, DL);
7915 break;
7916 case Instruction::FPToUI:
7917 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::UIToFP, C, SrcTy, DL);
7918 break;
7919 case Instruction::FPToSI:
7920 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::SIToFP, C, SrcTy, DL);
7921 break;
7922 case Instruction::UIToFP:
7923 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::FPToUI, C, SrcTy, DL);
7924 break;
7925 case Instruction::SIToFP:
7926 CastedTo = ConstantFoldCastOperand(Instruction::FPToSI, C, SrcTy, DL);
7927 break;
7928 default:
7929 break;
7930 }
7931
7932 if (!CastedTo)
7933 return nullptr;
7934
7935 // Make sure the cast doesn't lose any information.
7936 Constant *CastedBack =
7937 ConstantFoldCastOperand(*CastOp, CastedTo, C->getType(), DL);
7938 if (CastedBack && CastedBack != C)
7939 return nullptr;
7940
7941 return CastedTo;
7942}
7943
7944SelectPatternResult llvm::matchSelectPattern(Value *V, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
7945 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp,
7946 unsigned Depth) {
7947 if (Depth >= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
7948 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7949
7950 SelectInst *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V);
7951 if (!SI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7952
7953 CmpInst *CmpI = dyn_cast<CmpInst>(SI->getCondition());
7954 if (!CmpI) return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7955
7956 Value *TrueVal = SI->getTrueValue();
7957 Value *FalseVal = SI->getFalseValue();
7958
7959 return llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, LHS, RHS,
7960 CastOp, Depth);
7961}
7962
7963SelectPatternResult llvm::matchDecomposedSelectPattern(
7964 CmpInst *CmpI, Value *TrueVal, Value *FalseVal, Value *&LHS, Value *&RHS,
7965 Instruction::CastOps *CastOp, unsigned Depth) {
7966 CmpInst::Predicate Pred = CmpI->getPredicate();
7967 Value *CmpLHS = CmpI->getOperand(0);
7968 Value *CmpRHS = CmpI->getOperand(1);
7969 FastMathFlags FMF;
7970 if (isa<FPMathOperator>(CmpI))
7971 FMF = CmpI->getFastMathFlags();
7972
7973 // Bail out early.
7974 if (CmpI->isEquality())
7975 return {SPF_UNKNOWN, SPNB_NA, false};
7976
7977 // Deal with type mismatches.
7978 if (CastOp && CmpLHS->getType() != TrueVal->getType()) {
7979 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, TrueVal, FalseVal, CastOp)) {
7980 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
7981 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
7982 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
7983 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
7984 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
7985 cast<CastInst>(TrueVal)->getOperand(0), C,
7986 LHS, RHS, Depth);
7987 }
7988 if (Value *C = lookThroughCast(CmpI, FalseVal, TrueVal, CastOp)) {
7989 // If this is a potential fmin/fmax with a cast to integer, then ignore
7990 // -0.0 because there is no corresponding integer value.
7991 if (*CastOp == Instruction::FPToSI || *CastOp == Instruction::FPToUI)
7992 FMF.setNoSignedZeros();
7993 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS,
7994 C, cast<CastInst>(FalseVal)->getOperand(0),
7995 LHS, RHS, Depth);
7996 }
7997 }
7998 return ::matchSelectPattern(Pred, FMF, CmpLHS, CmpRHS, TrueVal, FalseVal,
7999 LHS, RHS, Depth);
8000}
8001
8002CmpInst::Predicate llvm::getMinMaxPred(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, bool Ordered) {
8003 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SLT;
8004 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT;
8005 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_SGT;
8006 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return ICmpInst::ICMP_UGT;
8007 if (SPF == SPF_FMINNUM)
8008 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OLT : FCmpInst::FCMP_ULT;
8009 if (SPF == SPF_FMAXNUM)
8010 return Ordered ? FCmpInst::FCMP_OGT : FCmpInst::FCMP_UGT;
8011 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
8012}
8013
8014SelectPatternFlavor llvm::getInverseMinMaxFlavor(SelectPatternFlavor SPF) {
8015 if (SPF == SPF_SMIN) return SPF_SMAX;
8016 if (SPF == SPF_UMIN) return SPF_UMAX;
8017 if (SPF == SPF_SMAX) return SPF_SMIN;
8018 if (SPF == SPF_UMAX) return SPF_UMIN;
8019 llvm_unreachable("unhandled!");
8020}
8021
8022Intrinsic::ID llvm::getInverseMinMaxIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ID MinMaxID) {
8023 switch (MinMaxID) {
8024 case Intrinsic::smax: return Intrinsic::smin;
8025 case Intrinsic::smin: return Intrinsic::smax;
8026 case Intrinsic::umax: return Intrinsic::umin;
8027 case Intrinsic::umin: return Intrinsic::umax;
8028 // Please note that next four intrinsics may produce the same result for
8029 // original and inverted case even if X != Y due to NaN is handled specially.
8030 case Intrinsic::maximum: return Intrinsic::minimum;
8031 case Intrinsic::minimum: return Intrinsic::maximum;
8032 case Intrinsic::maxnum: return Intrinsic::minnum;
8033 case Intrinsic::minnum: return Intrinsic::maxnum;
8034 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected intrinsic");
8035 }
8036}
8037
8038APInt llvm::getMinMaxLimit(SelectPatternFlavor SPF, unsigned BitWidth) {
8039 switch (SPF) {
8040 case SPF_SMAX: return APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth);
8041 case SPF_SMIN: return APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth);
8042 case SPF_UMAX: return APInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth);
8043 case SPF_UMIN: return APInt::getMinValue(BitWidth);
8044 default: llvm_unreachable("Unexpected flavor");
8045 }
8046}
8047
8048std::pair<Intrinsic::ID, bool>
8049llvm::canConvertToMinOrMaxIntrinsic(ArrayRef<Value *> VL) {
8050 // Check if VL contains select instructions that can be folded into a min/max
8051 // vector intrinsic and return the intrinsic if it is possible.
8052 // TODO: Support floating point min/max.
8053 bool AllCmpSingleUse = true;
8054 SelectPatternResult SelectPattern;
8055 SelectPattern.Flavor = SPF_UNKNOWN;
8056 if (all_of(VL, [&SelectPattern, &AllCmpSingleUse](Value *I) {
8057 Value *LHS, *RHS;
8058 auto CurrentPattern = matchSelectPattern(I, LHS, RHS);
8059 if (!SelectPatternResult::isMinOrMax(CurrentPattern.Flavor) ||
8060 CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMINNUM ||
8061 CurrentPattern.Flavor == SPF_FMAXNUM ||
8062 !I->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy())
8063 return false;
8064 if (SelectPattern.Flavor != SPF_UNKNOWN &&
8065 SelectPattern.Flavor != CurrentPattern.Flavor)
8066 return false;
8067 SelectPattern = CurrentPattern;
8068 AllCmpSingleUse &=
8069 match(I, m_Select(m_OneUse(m_Value()), m_Value(), m_Value()));
8070 return true;
8071 })) {
8072 switch (SelectPattern.Flavor) {
8073 case SPF_SMIN:
8074 return {Intrinsic::smin, AllCmpSingleUse};
8075 case SPF_UMIN:
8076 return {Intrinsic::umin, AllCmpSingleUse};
8077 case SPF_SMAX:
8078 return {Intrinsic::smax, AllCmpSingleUse};
8079 case SPF_UMAX:
8080 return {Intrinsic::umax, AllCmpSingleUse};
8081 default:
8082 llvm_unreachable("unexpected select pattern flavor");
8083 }
8084 }
8085 return {Intrinsic::not_intrinsic, false};
8086}
8087
8088bool llvm::matchSimpleRecurrence(const PHINode *P, BinaryOperator *&BO,
8089 Value *&Start, Value *&Step) {
8090 // Handle the case of a simple two-predecessor recurrence PHI.
8091 // There's a lot more that could theoretically be done here, but
8092 // this is sufficient to catch some interesting cases.
8093 if (P->getNumIncomingValues() != 2)
8094 return false;
8095
8096 for (unsigned i = 0; i != 2; ++i) {
8097 Value *L = P->getIncomingValue(i);
8098 Value *R = P->getIncomingValue(!i);
8099 auto *LU = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(L);
8100 if (!LU)
8101 continue;
8102 unsigned Opcode = LU->getOpcode();
8103
8104 switch (Opcode) {
8105 default:
8106 continue;
8107 // TODO: Expand list -- xor, div, gep, uaddo, etc..
8108 case Instruction::LShr:
8109 case Instruction::AShr:
8110 case Instruction::Shl:
8111 case Instruction::Add:
8112 case Instruction::Sub:
8113 case Instruction::And:
8114 case Instruction::Or:
8115 case Instruction::Mul:
8116 case Instruction::FMul: {
8117 Value *LL = LU->getOperand(0);
8118 Value *LR = LU->getOperand(1);
8119 // Find a recurrence.
8120 if (LL == P)
8121 L = LR;
8122 else if (LR == P)
8123 L = LL;
8124 else
8125 continue; // Check for recurrence with L and R flipped.
8126
8127 break; // Match!
8128 }
8129 };
8130
8131 // We have matched a recurrence of the form:
8132 // %iv = [R, %entry], [%iv.next, %backedge]
8133 // %iv.next = binop %iv, L
8134 // OR
8135 // %iv = [R, %entry], [%iv.next, %backedge]
8136 // %iv.next = binop L, %iv
8137 BO = LU;
8138 Start = R;
8139 Step = L;
8140 return true;
8141 }
8142 return false;
8143}
8144
8145bool llvm::matchSimpleRecurrence(const BinaryOperator *I, PHINode *&P,
8146 Value *&Start, Value *&Step) {
8147 BinaryOperator *BO = nullptr;
8148 P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I->getOperand(0));
8149 if (!P)
8150 P = dyn_cast<PHINode>(I->getOperand(1));
8151 return P && matchSimpleRecurrence(P, BO, Start, Step) && BO == I;
8152}
8153
8154/// Return true if "icmp Pred LHS RHS" is always true.
8155static bool isTruePredicate(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *LHS,
8156 const Value *RHS, const DataLayout &DL,
8157 unsigned Depth) {
8158 if (ICmpInst::isTrueWhenEqual(Pred) && LHS == RHS)
8159 return true;
8160
8161 switch (Pred) {
8162 default:
8163 return false;
8164
8165 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE: {
8166 const APInt *C;
8167
8168 // LHS s<= LHS +_{nsw} C if C >= 0
8169 if (match(RHS, m_NSWAdd(m_Specific(LHS), m_APInt(C))))
8170 return !C->isNegative();
8171 return false;
8172 }
8173
8174 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE: {
8175 // LHS u<= LHS +_{nuw} V for any V
8176 if (match(RHS, m_c_Add(m_Specific(LHS), m_Value())) &&
8177 cast<OverflowingBinaryOperator>(RHS)->hasNoUnsignedWrap())
8178 return true;
8179
8180 // RHS >> V u<= RHS for any V
8181 if (match(LHS, m_LShr(m_Specific(RHS), m_Value())))
8182 return true;
8183
8184 // Match A to (X +_{nuw} CA) and B to (X +_{nuw} CB)
8185 auto MatchNUWAddsToSameValue = [&](const Value *A, const Value *B,
8186 const Value *&X,
8187 const APInt *&CA, const APInt *&CB) {
8188 if (match(A, m_NUWAdd(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
8189 match(B, m_NUWAdd(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB))))
8190 return true;
8191
8192 // If X & C == 0 then (X | C) == X +_{nuw} C
8193 if (match(A, m_Or(m_Value(X), m_APInt(CA))) &&
8194 match(B, m_Or(m_Specific(X), m_APInt(CB)))) {
8195 KnownBits Known(CA->getBitWidth());
8196 computeKnownBits(X, Known, DL, Depth + 1, /*AC*/ nullptr,
8197 /*CxtI*/ nullptr, /*DT*/ nullptr);
8198 if (CA->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero) && CB->isSubsetOf(Known.Zero))
8199 return true;
8200 }
8201
8202 return false;
8203 };
8204
8205 const Value *X;
8206 const APInt *CLHS, *CRHS;
8207 if (MatchNUWAddsToSameValue(LHS, RHS, X, CLHS, CRHS))
8208 return CLHS->ule(*CRHS);
8209
8210 return false;
8211 }
8212 }
8213}
8214
8215/// Return true if "icmp Pred BLHS BRHS" is true whenever "icmp Pred
8216/// ALHS ARHS" is true. Otherwise, return std::nullopt.
8217static std::optional<bool>
8218isImpliedCondOperands(CmpInst::Predicate Pred, const Value *ALHS,
8219 const Value *ARHS, const Value *BLHS, const Value *BRHS,
8220 const DataLayout &DL, unsigned Depth) {
8221 switch (Pred) {
8222 default:
8223 return std::nullopt;
8224
8225 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLT:
8226 case CmpInst::ICMP_SLE:
8227 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
8228 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
8229 return true;
8230 return std::nullopt;
8231
8232 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGT:
8233 case CmpInst::ICMP_SGE:
8234 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, ALHS, BLHS, DL, Depth) &&
8235 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_SLE, BRHS, ARHS, DL, Depth))
8236 return true;
8237 return std::nullopt;
8238
8239 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULT:
8240 case CmpInst::ICMP_ULE:
8241 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, BLHS, ALHS, DL, Depth) &&
8242 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, ARHS, BRHS, DL, Depth))
8243 return true;
8244 return std::nullopt;
8245
8246 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGT:
8247 case CmpInst::ICMP_UGE:
8248 if (isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, ALHS, BLHS, DL, Depth) &&
8249 isTruePredicate(CmpInst::ICMP_ULE, BRHS, ARHS, DL, Depth))
8250 return true;
8251 return std::nullopt;
8252 }
8253}
8254
8255/// Return true if the operands of two compares (expanded as "L0 pred L1" and
8256/// "R0 pred R1") match. IsSwappedOps is true when the operands match, but are
8257/// swapped.
8258static bool areMatchingOperands(const Value *L0, const Value *L1, const Value *R0,
8259 const Value *R1, bool &AreSwappedOps) {
8260 bool AreMatchingOps = (L0 == R0 && L1 == R1);
8261 AreSwappedOps = (L0 == R1 && L1 == R0);
8262 return AreMatchingOps || AreSwappedOps;
8263}
8264
8265/// Return true if "icmp1 LPred X, Y" implies "icmp2 RPred X, Y" is true.
8266/// Return false if "icmp1 LPred X, Y" implies "icmp2 RPred X, Y" is false.
8267/// Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
8268static std::optional<bool>
8269isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(CmpInst::Predicate LPred,
8270 CmpInst::Predicate RPred, bool AreSwappedOps) {
8271 // Canonicalize the predicate as if the operands were not commuted.
8272 if (AreSwappedOps)
8273 RPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(RPred);
8274
8275 if (CmpInst::isImpliedTrueByMatchingCmp(LPred, RPred))
8276 return true;
8277 if (CmpInst::isImpliedFalseByMatchingCmp(LPred, RPred))
8278 return false;
8279
8280 return std::nullopt;
8281}
8282
8283/// Return true if "icmp LPred X, LC" implies "icmp RPred X, RC" is true.
8284/// Return false if "icmp LPred X, LC" implies "icmp RPred X, RC" is false.
8285/// Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
8286static std::optional<bool> isImpliedCondCommonOperandWithConstants(
8287 CmpInst::Predicate LPred, const APInt &LC, CmpInst::Predicate RPred,
8288 const APInt &RC) {
8289 ConstantRange DomCR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(LPred, LC);
8290 ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::makeExactICmpRegion(RPred, RC);
8291 ConstantRange Intersection = DomCR.intersectWith(CR);
8292 ConstantRange Difference = DomCR.difference(CR);
8293 if (Intersection.isEmptySet())
8294 return false;
8295 if (Difference.isEmptySet())
8296 return true;
8297 return std::nullopt;
8298}
8299
8300/// Return true if LHS implies RHS (expanded to its components as "R0 RPred R1")
8301/// is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is false. Otherwise, return
8302/// std::nullopt if we can't infer anything.
8303static std::optional<bool> isImpliedCondICmps(const ICmpInst *LHS,
8304 CmpInst::Predicate RPred,
8305 const Value *R0, const Value *R1,
8306 const DataLayout &DL,
8307 bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
8308 Value *L0 = LHS->getOperand(0);
8309 Value *L1 = LHS->getOperand(1);
8310
8311 // The rest of the logic assumes the LHS condition is true. If that's not the
8312 // case, invert the predicate to make it so.
8313 CmpInst::Predicate LPred =
8314 LHSIsTrue ? LHS->getPredicate() : LHS->getInversePredicate();
8315
8316 // Can we infer anything when the 0-operands match and the 1-operands are
8317 // constants (not necessarily matching)?
8318 const APInt *LC, *RC;
8319 if (L0 == R0 && match(L1, m_APInt(LC)) && match(R1, m_APInt(RC)))
8320 return isImpliedCondCommonOperandWithConstants(LPred, *LC, RPred, *RC);
8321
8322 // Can we infer anything when the two compares have matching operands?
8323 bool AreSwappedOps;
8324 if (areMatchingOperands(L0, L1, R0, R1, AreSwappedOps))
8325 return isImpliedCondMatchingOperands(LPred, RPred, AreSwappedOps);
8326
8327 // L0 = R0 = L1 + R1, L0 >=u L1 implies R0 >=u R1, L0 <u L1 implies R0 <u R1
8328 if (ICmpInst::isUnsigned(LPred) && ICmpInst::isUnsigned(RPred)) {
8329 if (L0 == R1) {
8330 std::swap(R0, R1);
8331 RPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(RPred);
8332 }
8333 if (L1 == R0) {
8334 std::swap(L0, L1);
8335 LPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(LPred);
8336 }
8337 if (L1 == R1) {
8338 std::swap(L0, L1);
8339 LPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(LPred);
8340 std::swap(R0, R1);
8341 RPred = ICmpInst::getSwappedPredicate(RPred);
8342 }
8343 if (L0 == R0 &&
8344 (LPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || LPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) &&
8345 (RPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_ULT || RPred == ICmpInst::ICMP_UGE) &&
8346 match(L0, m_c_Add(m_Specific(L1), m_Specific(R1))))
8347 return LPred == RPred;
8348 }
8349
8350 if (LPred == RPred)
8351 return isImpliedCondOperands(LPred, L0, L1, R0, R1, DL, Depth);
8352
8353 return std::nullopt;
8354}
8355
8356/// Return true if LHS implies RHS is true. Return false if LHS implies RHS is
8357/// false. Otherwise, return std::nullopt if we can't infer anything. We
8358/// expect the RHS to be an icmp and the LHS to be an 'and', 'or', or a 'select'
8359/// instruction.
8360static std::optional<bool>
8361isImpliedCondAndOr(const Instruction *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
8362 const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
8363 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
8364 // The LHS must be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction.
8365 assert((LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
8366 LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
8367 LHS->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select) &&
8368 "Expected LHS to be 'and', 'or', or 'select'.");
8369
8370 assert(Depth <= MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth && "Hit recursion limit");
8371
8372 // If the result of an 'or' is false, then we know both legs of the 'or' are
8373 // false. Similarly, if the result of an 'and' is true, then we know both
8374 // legs of the 'and' are true.
8375 const Value *ALHS, *ARHS;
8376 if ((!LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS)))) ||
8377 (LHSIsTrue && match(LHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(ALHS), m_Value(ARHS))))) {
8378 // FIXME: Make this non-recursion.
8379 if (std::optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
8380 ALHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8381 return Implication;
8382 if (std::optional<bool> Implication = isImpliedCondition(
8383 ARHS, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8384 return Implication;
8385 return std::nullopt;
8386 }
8387 return std::nullopt;
8388}
8389
8390std::optional<bool>
8391llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, CmpInst::Predicate RHSPred,
8392 const Value *RHSOp0, const Value *RHSOp1,
8393 const DataLayout &DL, bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
8394 // Bail out when we hit the limit.
8395 if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
8396 return std::nullopt;
8397
8398 // A mismatch occurs when we compare a scalar cmp to a vector cmp, for
8399 // example.
8400 if (RHSOp0->getType()->isVectorTy() != LHS->getType()->isVectorTy())
8401 return std::nullopt;
8402
8403 assert(LHS->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) &&
8404 "Expected integer type only!");
8405
8406 // Both LHS and RHS are icmps.
8407 const ICmpInst *LHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(LHS);
8408 if (LHSCmp)
8409 return isImpliedCondICmps(LHSCmp, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
8410 Depth);
8411
8412 /// The LHS should be an 'or', 'and', or a 'select' instruction. We expect
8413 /// the RHS to be an icmp.
8414 /// FIXME: Add support for and/or/select on the RHS.
8415 if (const Instruction *LHSI = dyn_cast<Instruction>(LHS)) {
8416 if ((LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::And ||
8417 LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Or ||
8418 LHSI->getOpcode() == Instruction::Select))
8419 return isImpliedCondAndOr(LHSI, RHSPred, RHSOp0, RHSOp1, DL, LHSIsTrue,
8420 Depth);
8421 }
8422 return std::nullopt;
8423}
8424
8425std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedCondition(const Value *LHS, const Value *RHS,
8426 const DataLayout &DL,
8427 bool LHSIsTrue, unsigned Depth) {
8428 // LHS ==> RHS by definition
8429 if (LHS == RHS)
8430 return LHSIsTrue;
8431
8432 if (const ICmpInst *RHSCmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(RHS))
8433 return isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHSCmp->getPredicate(),
8434 RHSCmp->getOperand(0), RHSCmp->getOperand(1), DL,
8435 LHSIsTrue, Depth);
8436
8437 if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
8438 return std::nullopt;
8439
8440 // LHS ==> (RHS1 || RHS2) if LHS ==> RHS1 or LHS ==> RHS2
8441 // LHS ==> !(RHS1 && RHS2) if LHS ==> !RHS1 or LHS ==> !RHS2
8442 const Value *RHS1, *RHS2;
8443 if (match(RHS, m_LogicalOr(m_Value(RHS1), m_Value(RHS2)))) {
8444 if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
8445 isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8446 if (*Imp == true)
8447 return true;
8448 if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
8449 isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS2, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8450 if (*Imp == true)
8451 return true;
8452 }
8453 if (match(RHS, m_LogicalAnd(m_Value(RHS1), m_Value(RHS2)))) {
8454 if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
8455 isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS1, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8456 if (*Imp == false)
8457 return false;
8458 if (std::optional<bool> Imp =
8459 isImpliedCondition(LHS, RHS2, DL, LHSIsTrue, Depth + 1))
8460 if (*Imp == false)
8461 return false;
8462 }
8463
8464 return std::nullopt;
8465}
8466
8467// Returns a pair (Condition, ConditionIsTrue), where Condition is a branch
8468// condition dominating ContextI or nullptr, if no condition is found.
8469static std::pair<Value *, bool>
8470getDomPredecessorCondition(const Instruction *ContextI) {
8471 if (!ContextI || !ContextI->getParent())
8472 return {nullptr, false};
8473
8474 // TODO: This is a poor/cheap way to determine dominance. Should we use a
8475 // dominator tree (eg, from a SimplifyQuery) instead?
8476 const BasicBlock *ContextBB = ContextI->getParent();
8477 const BasicBlock *PredBB = ContextBB->getSinglePredecessor();
8478 if (!PredBB)
8479 return {nullptr, false};
8480
8481 // We need a conditional branch in the predecessor.
8482 Value *PredCond;
8483 BasicBlock *TrueBB, *FalseBB;
8484 if (!match(PredBB->getTerminator(), m_Br(m_Value(PredCond), TrueBB, FalseBB)))
8485 return {nullptr, false};
8486
8487 // The branch should get simplified. Don't bother simplifying this condition.
8488 if (TrueBB == FalseBB)
8489 return {nullptr, false};
8490
8491 assert((TrueBB == ContextBB || FalseBB == ContextBB) &&
8492 "Predecessor block does not point to successor?");
8493
8494 // Is this condition implied by the predecessor condition?
8495 return {PredCond, TrueBB == ContextBB};
8496}
8497
8498std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(const Value *Cond,
8499 const Instruction *ContextI,
8500 const DataLayout &DL) {
8501 assert(Cond->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy(1) && "Condition must be bool");
8502 auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
8503 if (PredCond.first)
8504 return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Cond, DL, PredCond.second);
8505 return std::nullopt;
8506}
8507
8508std::optional<bool> llvm::isImpliedByDomCondition(CmpInst::Predicate Pred,
8509 const Value *LHS,
8510 const Value *RHS,
8511 const Instruction *ContextI,
8512 const DataLayout &DL) {
8513 auto PredCond = getDomPredecessorCondition(ContextI);
8514 if (PredCond.first)
8515 return isImpliedCondition(PredCond.first, Pred, LHS, RHS, DL,
8516 PredCond.second);
8517 return std::nullopt;
8518}
8519
8520static void setLimitsForBinOp(const BinaryOperator &BO, APInt &Lower,
8521 APInt &Upper, const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ,
8522 bool PreferSignedRange) {
8523 unsigned Width = Lower.getBitWidth();
8524 const APInt *C;
8525 switch (BO.getOpcode()) {
8526 case Instruction::Add:
8527 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isZero()) {
8528 bool HasNSW = IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(&BO);
8529 bool HasNUW = IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO);
8530
8531 // If the caller expects a signed compare, then try to use a signed range.
8532 // Otherwise if both no-wraps are set, use the unsigned range because it
8533 // is never larger than the signed range. Example:
8534 // "add nuw nsw i8 X, -2" is unsigned [254,255] vs. signed [-128, 125].
8535 if (PreferSignedRange && HasNSW && HasNUW)
8536 HasNUW = false;
8537
8538 if (HasNUW) {
8539 // 'add nuw x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
8540 Lower = *C;
8541 } else if (HasNSW) {
8542 if (C->isNegative()) {
8543 // 'add nsw x, -C' produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
8544 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
8545 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C + 1;
8546 } else {
8547 // 'add nsw x, +C' produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
8548 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C;
8549 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1;
8550 }
8551 }
8552 }
8553 break;
8554
8555 case Instruction::And:
8556 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8557 // 'and x, C' produces [0, C].
8558 Upper = *C + 1;
8559 // X & -X is a power of two or zero. So we can cap the value at max power of
8560 // two.
8561 if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_Neg(m_Specific(BO.getOperand(1)))) ||
8562 match(BO.getOperand(1), m_Neg(m_Specific(BO.getOperand(0)))))
8563 Upper = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1;
8564 break;
8565
8566 case Instruction::Or:
8567 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8568 // 'or x, C' produces [C, UINT_MAX].
8569 Lower = *C;
8570 break;
8571
8572 case Instruction::AShr:
8573 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
8574 // 'ashr x, C' produces [INT_MIN >> C, INT_MAX >> C].
8575 Lower = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width).ashr(*C);
8576 Upper = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width).ashr(*C) + 1;
8577 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
8578 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
8579 if (!C->isZero() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
8580 ShiftAmount = C->countr_zero();
8581 if (C->isNegative()) {
8582 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C, C >> (Width-1)]
8583 Lower = *C;
8584 Upper = C->ashr(ShiftAmount) + 1;
8585 } else {
8586 // 'ashr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C]
8587 Lower = C->ashr(ShiftAmount);
8588 Upper = *C + 1;
8589 }
8590 }
8591 break;
8592
8593 case Instruction::LShr:
8594 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
8595 // 'lshr x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX >> C].
8596 Upper = APInt::getAllOnes(Width).lshr(*C) + 1;
8597 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
8598 // 'lshr C, x' produces [C >> (Width-1), C].
8599 unsigned ShiftAmount = Width - 1;
8600 if (!C->isZero() && IIQ.isExact(&BO))
8601 ShiftAmount = C->countr_zero();
8602 Lower = C->lshr(ShiftAmount);
8603 Upper = *C + 1;
8604 }
8605 break;
8606
8607 case Instruction::Shl:
8608 if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
8609 if (IIQ.hasNoUnsignedWrap(&BO)) {
8610 // 'shl nuw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)]
8611 Lower = *C;
8612 Upper = Lower.shl(Lower.countl_zero()) + 1;
8613 } else if (BO.hasNoSignedWrap()) { // TODO: What if both nuw+nsw?
8614 if (C->isNegative()) {
8615 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C << CLO(C)-1, C]
8616 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countl_one() - 1;
8617 Lower = C->shl(ShiftAmount);
8618 Upper = *C + 1;
8619 } else {
8620 // 'shl nsw C, x' produces [C, C << CLZ(C)-1]
8621 unsigned ShiftAmount = C->countl_zero() - 1;
8622 Lower = *C;
8623 Upper = C->shl(ShiftAmount) + 1;
8624 }
8625 } else {
8626 // If lowbit is set, value can never be zero.
8627 if ((*C)[0])
8628 Lower = APInt::getOneBitSet(Width, 0);
8629 // If we are shifting a constant the largest it can be is if the longest
8630 // sequence of consecutive ones is shifted to the highbits (breaking
8631 // ties for which sequence is higher). At the moment we take a liberal
8632 // upper bound on this by just popcounting the constant.
8633 // TODO: There may be a bitwise trick for it longest/highest
8634 // consecutative sequence of ones (naive method is O(Width) loop).
8635 Upper = APInt::getHighBitsSet(Width, C->popcount()) + 1;
8636 }
8637 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && C->ult(Width)) {
8638 Upper = APInt::getBitsSetFrom(Width, C->getZExtValue()) + 1;
8639 }
8640 break;
8641
8642 case Instruction::SDiv:
8643 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
8644 APInt IntMin = APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width);
8645 APInt IntMax = APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width);
8646 if (C->isAllOnes()) {
8647 // 'sdiv x, -1' produces [INT_MIN + 1, INT_MAX]
8648 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
8649 Lower = IntMin + 1;
8650 Upper = IntMax + 1;
8651 } else if (C->countl_zero() < Width - 1) {
8652 // 'sdiv x, C' produces [INT_MIN / C, INT_MAX / C]
8653 // where C != -1 and C != 0 and C != 1
8654 Lower = IntMin.sdiv(*C);
8655 Upper = IntMax.sdiv(*C);
8656 if (Lower.sgt(Upper))
8657 std::swap(Lower, Upper);
8658 Upper = Upper + 1;
8659 assert(Upper != Lower && "Upper part of range has wrapped!");
8660 }
8661 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
8662 if (C->isMinSignedValue()) {
8663 // 'sdiv INT_MIN, x' produces [INT_MIN, INT_MIN / -2].
8664 Lower = *C;
8665 Upper = Lower.lshr(1) + 1;
8666 } else {
8667 // 'sdiv C, x' produces [-|C|, |C|].
8668 Upper = C->abs() + 1;
8669 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
8670 }
8671 }
8672 break;
8673
8674 case Instruction::UDiv:
8675 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)) && !C->isZero()) {
8676 // 'udiv x, C' produces [0, UINT_MAX / C].
8677 Upper = APInt::getMaxValue(Width).udiv(*C) + 1;
8678 } else if (match(BO.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
8679 // 'udiv C, x' produces [0, C].
8680 Upper = *C + 1;
8681 }
8682 break;
8683
8684 case Instruction::SRem:
8685 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
8686 // 'srem x, C' produces (-|C|, |C|).
8687 Upper = C->abs();
8688 Lower = (-Upper) + 1;
8689 }
8690 break;
8691
8692 case Instruction::URem:
8693 if (match(BO.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8694 // 'urem x, C' produces [0, C).
8695 Upper = *C;
8696 break;
8697
8698 default:
8699 break;
8700 }
8701}
8702
8703static ConstantRange getRangeForIntrinsic(const IntrinsicInst &II) {
8704 unsigned Width = II.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
8705 const APInt *C;
8706 switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
8707 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
8708 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
8709 case Intrinsic::cttz:
8710 // Maximum of set/clear bits is the bit width.
8711 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width),
8712 APInt(Width, Width + 1));
8713 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
8714 // uadd.sat(x, C) produces [C, UINT_MAX].
8715 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
8716 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8717 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C, APInt::getZero(Width));
8718 break;
8719 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
8720 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) ||
8721 match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
8722 if (C->isNegative())
8723 // sadd.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX + (-C)].
8724 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width),
8725 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + *C +
8726 1);
8727
8728 // sadd.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN + C, SINT_MAX].
8729 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + *C,
8730 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1);
8731 }
8732 break;
8733 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
8734 // usub.sat(C, x) produces [0, C].
8735 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)))
8736 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width), *C + 1);
8737
8738 // usub.sat(x, C) produces [0, UINT_MAX - C].
8739 if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8740 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width),
8741 APInt::getMaxValue(Width) - *C + 1);
8742 break;
8743 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
8744 if (match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C))) {
