8745 if (C->isNegative())
8746 // ssub.sat(-C, x) produces [SINT_MIN, -SINT_MIN + (-C)].
8747 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width),
8748 *C - APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) +
8749 1);
8750
8751 // ssub.sat(+C, x) produces [-SINT_MAX + C, SINT_MAX].
8752 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C - APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width),
8753 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1);
8754 } else if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C))) {
8755 if (C->isNegative())
8756 // ssub.sat(x, -C) produces [SINT_MIN - (-C), SINT_MAX]:
8757 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) - *C,
8758 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1);
8759
8760 // ssub.sat(x, +C) produces [SINT_MIN, SINT_MAX - C].
8761 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width),
8762 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) - *C +
8763 1);
8764 }
8765 break;
8766 case Intrinsic::umin:
8767 case Intrinsic::umax:
8768 case Intrinsic::smin:
8769 case Intrinsic::smax:
8770 if (!match(II.getOperand(0), m_APInt(C)) &&
8771 !match(II.getOperand(1), m_APInt(C)))
8772 break;
8773
8774 switch (II.getIntrinsicID()) {
8775 case Intrinsic::umin:
8776 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width), *C + 1);
8777 case Intrinsic::umax:
8778 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C, APInt::getZero(Width));
8779 case Intrinsic::smin:
8780 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width),
8781 *C + 1);
8782 case Intrinsic::smax:
8783 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C,
8784 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1);
8785 default:
8786 llvm_unreachable("Must be min/max intrinsic");
8787 }
8788 break;
8789 case Intrinsic::abs:
8790 // If abs of SIGNED_MIN is poison, then the result is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
8791 // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
8792 if (match(II.getOperand(1), m_One()))
8793 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width),
8794 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width) + 1);
8795
8796 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(Width),
8797 APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width) + 1);
8798 case Intrinsic::vscale:
8799 if (!II.getParent() || !II.getFunction())
8800 break;
8801 return getVScaleRange(II.getFunction(), Width);
8802 default:
8803 break;
8804 }
8805
8806 return ConstantRange::getFull(Width);
8807}
8808
8809static ConstantRange getRangeForSelectPattern(const SelectInst &SI,
8810 const InstrInfoQuery &IIQ) {
8811 unsigned BitWidth = SI.getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
8812 const Value *LHS = nullptr, *RHS = nullptr;
8813 SelectPatternResult R = matchSelectPattern(&SI, LHS, RHS);
8814 if (R.Flavor == SPF_UNKNOWN)
8815 return ConstantRange::getFull(BitWidth);
8816
8817 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_ABS) {
8818 // If the negation part of the abs (in RHS) has the NSW flag,
8819 // then the result of abs(X) is [0..SIGNED_MAX],
8820 // otherwise it is [0..SIGNED_MIN], as -SIGNED_MIN == SIGNED_MIN.
8821 if (match(RHS, m_Neg(m_Specific(LHS))) &&
8822 IIQ.hasNoSignedWrap(cast<Instruction>(RHS)))
8823 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(BitWidth),
8824 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1);
8825
8826 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(BitWidth),
8827 APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth) + 1);
8828 }
8829
8830 if (R.Flavor == SelectPatternFlavor::SPF_NABS) {
8831 // The result of -abs(X) is <= 0.
8832 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth),
8833 APInt(BitWidth, 1));
8834 }
8835
8836 const APInt *C;
8837 if (!match(LHS, m_APInt(C)) && !match(RHS, m_APInt(C)))
8838 return ConstantRange::getFull(BitWidth);
8839
8840 switch (R.Flavor) {
8841 case SPF_UMIN:
8842 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getZero(BitWidth), *C + 1);
8843 case SPF_UMAX:
8844 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C, APInt::getZero(BitWidth));
8845 case SPF_SMIN:
8846 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth),
8847 *C + 1);
8848 case SPF_SMAX:
8849 return ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(*C,
8850 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth) + 1);
8851 default:
8852 return ConstantRange::getFull(BitWidth);
8853 }
8854}
8855
8856static void setLimitForFPToI(const Instruction *I, APInt &Lower, APInt &Upper) {
8857 // The maximum representable value of a half is 65504. For floats the maximum
8858 // value is 3.4e38 which requires roughly 129 bits.
8859 unsigned BitWidth = I->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
8860 if (!I->getOperand(0)->getType()->getScalarType()->isHalfTy())
8861 return;
8862 if (isa<FPToSIInst>(I) && BitWidth >= 17) {
8863 Lower = APInt(BitWidth, -65504);
8864 Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 65505);
8865 }
8866
8867 if (isa<FPToUIInst>(I) && BitWidth >= 16) {
8868 // For a fptoui the lower limit is left as 0.
8869 Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 65505);
8870 }
8871}
8872
8873ConstantRange llvm::computeConstantRange(const Value *V, bool ForSigned,
8874 bool UseInstrInfo, AssumptionCache *AC,
8875 const Instruction *CtxI,
8876 const DominatorTree *DT,
8877 unsigned Depth) {
8878 assert(V->getType()->isIntOrIntVectorTy() && "Expected integer instruction");
8879
8880 if (Depth == MaxAnalysisRecursionDepth)
8881 return ConstantRange::getFull(V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits());
8882
8883 const APInt *C;
8884 if (match(V, m_APInt(C)))
8885 return ConstantRange(*C);
8886 unsigned BitWidth = V->getType()->getScalarSizeInBits();
8887
8888 if (auto *VC = dyn_cast<ConstantDataVector>(V)) {
8889 ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::getEmpty(BitWidth);
8890 for (unsigned ElemIdx = 0, NElem = VC->getNumElements(); ElemIdx < NElem;
8891 ++ElemIdx)
8892 CR = CR.unionWith(VC->getElementAsAPInt(ElemIdx));
8893 return CR;
8894 }
8895
8896 InstrInfoQuery IIQ(UseInstrInfo);
8897 ConstantRange CR = ConstantRange::getFull(BitWidth);
8898 if (auto *BO = dyn_cast<BinaryOperator>(V)) {
8899 APInt Lower = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
8900 APInt Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
8901 // TODO: Return ConstantRange.
8902 setLimitsForBinOp(*BO, Lower, Upper, IIQ, ForSigned);
8903 CR = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Lower, Upper);
8904 } else if (auto *II = dyn_cast<IntrinsicInst>(V))
8905 CR = getRangeForIntrinsic(*II);
8906 else if (auto *SI = dyn_cast<SelectInst>(V)) {
8907 ConstantRange CRTrue = computeConstantRange(
8908 SI->getTrueValue(), ForSigned, UseInstrInfo, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth + 1);
8909 ConstantRange CRFalse = computeConstantRange(
8910 SI->getFalseValue(), ForSigned, UseInstrInfo, AC, CtxI, DT, Depth + 1);
8911 CR = CRTrue.unionWith(CRFalse);
8912 CR = CR.intersectWith(getRangeForSelectPattern(*SI, IIQ));
8913 } else if (isa<FPToUIInst>(V) || isa<FPToSIInst>(V)) {
8914 APInt Lower = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
8915 APInt Upper = APInt(BitWidth, 0);
8916 // TODO: Return ConstantRange.
8917 setLimitForFPToI(cast<Instruction>(V), Lower, Upper);
8918 CR = ConstantRange::getNonEmpty(Lower, Upper);
8919 }
8920
8921 if (auto *I = dyn_cast<Instruction>(V))
8922 if (auto *Range = IIQ.getMetadata(I, LLVMContext::MD_range))
8923 CR = CR.intersectWith(getConstantRangeFromMetadata(*Range));
8924
8925 if (CtxI && AC) {
8926 // Try to restrict the range based on information from assumptions.
8927 for (auto &AssumeVH : AC->assumptionsFor(V)) {
8928 if (!AssumeVH)
8929 continue;
8930 CallInst *I = cast<CallInst>(AssumeVH);
8931 assert(I->getParent()->getParent() == CtxI->getParent()->getParent() &&
8932 "Got assumption for the wrong function!");
8933 assert(I->getCalledFunction()->getIntrinsicID() == Intrinsic::assume &&
8934 "must be an assume intrinsic");
8935
8936 if (!isValidAssumeForContext(I, CtxI, DT))
8937 continue;
8938 Value *Arg = I->getArgOperand(0);
8939 ICmpInst *Cmp = dyn_cast<ICmpInst>(Arg);
8940 // Currently we just use information from comparisons.
8941 if (!Cmp || Cmp->getOperand(0) != V)
8942 continue;
8943 // TODO: Set "ForSigned" parameter via Cmp->isSigned()?
8944 ConstantRange RHS =
8945 computeConstantRange(Cmp->getOperand(1), /* ForSigned */ false,
8946 UseInstrInfo, AC, I, DT, Depth + 1);
8947 CR = CR.intersectWith(
8948 ConstantRange::makeAllowedICmpRegion(Cmp->getPredicate(), RHS));
8949 }
8950 }
8951
8952 return CR;
8953}
